SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MSC REALTY, INC.(THE ORGANIZATION) QUALIFIES AS A TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION UNDER SECTION 501(C)(2) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (THE "IRC"). AS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ENTITY, THE ORGANIZATION IS SUBJECT TO UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME TAX ("UBIT"), IF APPLICABLE. IN ACCORDANCE WITH FASB ASC 740, INCOME TAXES, THE ORGANIZATION APPLIES THE "MORE LIKELY THAN NOT" THRESHOLD TO THE RECOGNITION AND DERECOGNITION OF TAX POSITIONS FOR ITS CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX POSISTIONS AND HAS CONCLUDED THAT THERE WERE NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT QUALIFIED FOR EITHER RECOGNITION OR DISCLOSURE IN THESE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

THE PRESIDENT OF MSC REALTY, INC. IS EMPLOYED BY MEETING STREET, A RI NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATION AND AN ENTITY RELATED TO MSC REALTY, INC. THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES OF MEETING STREET, A RI NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATION, HAS A COMPENSATION COMMITTEE WHICH PERFORMS THE ANNUAL EVALUATION AND SETS THE COMPENSATION FOR THE PRESIDENT. THE PRESIDENT IS RESPONSIBLE FOR DETERMINING COMPENSATION FOR TOP MANAGEMENT POSITIONS AND WILL CONSULT WITH THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE REGARDING ADDITIONAL MATERIAL COMPENSATION ARRANGEMENTS

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY AND APPROVED BY THE FINANCE/AUDIT COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES BEFORE FILING. A COPY OF THE 990 IS ALSO PROVIDED TO ALL MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH TRUSTEE MUST SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST ACKNOWLEDGEMENT UPON COMMENCEMENT OF ASSOCIATION. TRUSTEES: ANY TRUSTEE WHO MAY BE INVOLVED IN AN MSC REALTY, INC. BUSINESS TRANSACTION IN WHICH THERE IS A POSSIBLE CONFLICT OF INTEREST SHALL PROMPTLY NOTIFY THE CHAIR OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES. THE TRUSTEE WILL REFRAIN FROM VOTING ON SUCH MATTER AND THE TRUSTEE, OR THE CHAIR IN THE TRUSTEE'S ABSENCE, WILL DISCLOSE THE POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST TO THE OTHER BOARD MEMBERS BEFORE THE VOTE TAKES PLACE AND SUCH DISCLOSURES SHALL BE RECORDED IN THE BOARD MINUTES. ANY TRANSACTION INVOLVING A POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST SHALL HAVE TERMS THAT ARE FAIR AND REASONABLE AS THOUGH MSC REALTY, INC. WERE DEALING WITH AN UNRELATED PARTY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PUBLIC CAN OBTAIN A COPY OF THE 990 UPON REQUEST TO THE ORGANIZATION. THE PUBLIC CAN OBTAIN DOCUMENTATION UPON REQUEST.
